President Trump addressed community leaders and representatives from the Drug-Free Communities initiative in the Roosevelt Room. He announced that his administration is providing a record $91 million in grants to support the initiative, impacting more communities than ever before. The Drug-Free Communities program has been successful in reducing alcohol and prescription drug abuse among high school students by nearly 20%. The President also highlighted the ongoing efforts to combat the opioid crisis, including a reduction in high-dose opioid prescriptions and increased funding. He expressed his support for holding drug traffickers accountable and praised the work of community coalitions and youth representatives in fighting substance abuse. The President also briefly discussed trade talks with Canada and China, as well as his concerns about Google and other social media platforms treating conservatives unfairly.